# gen30: cause/effect reasoning — a directed relation causes(a, b) parrot0
# never had, pulled by the first SuperGLUE COPA question ("The man turned on
# the faucet. effect: toilet filled / water flowed"). We test the relation and
# the COPA-shaped two-way chooser over STATED causal facts; commonsense
# causality (knowing a faucet produces water) is out of scope.
> faucet causes water
< Learned: causes(faucet, water).
> rain causes flood
< Learned: causes(rain, flood).
> what is the effect of faucet?
< water.
> what is the cause of flood?
< rain.
# The COPA shape: pick the candidate that is the known effect / cause.
> effect of faucet: toilet or water?
< water.
> cause of flood: rain or moon?
< rain.
# Neither candidate qualifies -> say so, don't guess.
> effect of faucet: toilet or sink?
< Neither.
# Unknown direction is admitted.
> what is the effect of moon?
< I don't know the effect of moon.